ibrary at Nanterre</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_44563b58ed65ce215ae215d3865c4554" level="file"><did><unittitle>PRO - PREM 314 + FO</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1945/1945">1945</unitdate><container id="aspace_9b7ebc7bf105f47b824c7c998d3dbf26" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_3d3ac030d61236714b9ae3327f18b46b" parent="aspace_9b7ebc7bf105f47b824c7c998d3dbf26" type="folder">5-6</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_669fb89da0b2e7f65b08d266a15294ea"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Classified documents on French Indo-China from Public Records Office (Foreign Office documents)</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_40e26f05a69d014871b2b4106e486296" level="file"><did><unittitle>Mary Speers' Notes</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1942/1943" type="inclusive">1942-1943</unitdate><container id="aspace_d503d296b54dd979db2b4ea0df0c865e" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_b41b711e1c4a1c2104d7ed5c8543c4e1" parent="aspace_d503d296b54dd979db2b4ea0df0c865e" type="folder">7</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_2fb37c646720f4ad11ac37885ab965b4"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Foreign Office series 371/35921, ff. Mostly on wartime relations with France.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_66374441566d62f006507bd57881470f" level="file"><did><unittitle>My Notes 1980 - PRO &amp; Rhodes House</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1980/1980">1980</unitdate><container id="aspace_69119556565d03e649e1578a761b6c3e" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_1e5bff586310310f90c64ca5a7a0da4e" parent="aspace_69119556565d03e649e1578a761b6c3e" type="folder">8</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_15da68ac1d332fa320352b6d9de99815"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>CAB 121/741 - Notes taken on memos on Indochina for PM from Foreign Section. File: "My Notes 1980: PRO &amp; Roosevelt." CAB 120/56 - 121/741. Succinct notes of heart of documents re: French Indochina (ca. 40-50 pp.). Notebook cover headed "Cabinet Officers etc." has several pages of references to A. Creech Jones.</p><p> 2nd notebook: Rhodes Library Oxford - About 100 pp. of penciled notes on FO 371; CO 824 Register; CO 872-4-9 inclusive (1942, 1942) Mostly to FO 371/371779-90</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_882641775d4bd943c4046cce71f4aac7" level="file"><did><unittitle>DDE '54 - documents</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1954/1954">1954</unitdate><container id="aspace_c8df65b15aaae0151a3e708b32abb81a" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_87ca6a68f8857767cc761e21f23ef840" parent="aspace_c8df65b15aaae0151a3e708b32abb81a" type="folder">9</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_d4c4cd2d8b44f1177511b9a1ffa9da65"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Dwight D. Eisenhower Library</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_42adfae9cae0b88bcf98f8b0bf2e8c14" level="file"><did><unittitle>National Archives - Use of Indo China Resistance Forces</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1944/1945" type="inclusive">1944-1945</unitdate><container id="aspace_6544053d479d41cfbbb6538301e4f6e5" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_bf7c60607414bd5cc98fb2ab087392f6" parent="aspace_6544053d479d41cfbbb6538301e4f6e5" type="folder">10-11</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_dbd8f8d86f47433c2d61b3b65e326d31" level="file"><did><unittitle>National Archives</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1941/1941">1941</unitdate><container id="aspace_8c1d20bf5ca4854eb73611d786b4a873" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_ba7dfe00dc38b9ca3e48e44bc10fef28" parent="aspace_8c1d20bf5ca4854eb73611d786b4a873" type="folder">12</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_88f942e2113e